			  	Guys, this is a game and as such it is (in theory) designed to be fun.  Priorities:  1.  Fun - 2.  Realism.  Do not sacrifice fun for the sake of realism or you are contradicting the main point of the game.  Archspace is not used to train future military geniuses; it is used for entertainment, so whether or not the game is realistic only matters if the game is fun in the first place.  I could make a game about sitting through science class, and it could be very realistic but who would play a game based on sitting through a science class?  That said I think almost everyone realizes the problems with blockading, and honor being meaningless, and there have been countless posts on these subjects.  At this point I'm just waiting to see how/whether the mods respond.			   <P align=right></P>
